name: lunarcalendar
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "LunarCalendar" %}
{% set version = "0.0.9" %}

package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 681142f22fc353c3abca4b25699e3d1aa7083ad1c268dce36ba297eca04bed5a

build:
  number: 0
  noarch: python
  entry_points:
    - lunar-find = lunarcalendar.command:find
  script: "{{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . -vv"

requirements:
  host:
    - python
    - pip
    - python-dateutil >=2.8.0
    - ephem >=3.7.5.3
    - pytz
  run:
    - python
    - python-dateutil >=2.8.0
    - ephem >=3.7.5.3
    - pytz

test:
  imports:
    - lunarcalendar

about:
  home: https://github.com/wolfhong/LunarCalendar
  license: MIT
  license_family: MIT
  license_file: LICENSE
  summary: 'A lunar calendar converter, including a number of lunar and solar holidays, mainly from China.'


extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - bletham
